{{distinguish|Paolo Acerbis}} {{Infobox company | name = Acerbis S.p.A. | logo = File:Acerbis logo.svg | type = [[Privately held company|Private]] | foundation = {{start date|1973}} | location_city = [[Albino]], [[Province of Bergamo|Bergamo]] | location_country = Italy | key_people = | industry = [[Clothing]] | products = {{unbulleted list|[[Sportswear (activewear)|Sportswear]]|[[Sports equipment|Sports Goods]]}} | revenue = | num_employees = | homepage = {{unbulleted list|{{official website|www.acerbis.it|name=www.acerbis.it}}}} }}
'''Acerbis S.p.A.''' is an Italian sports gear manufacturer. Besides, Acerbis is a manufacturer and supplier of various motorcycle gear, parts and equipment. Some of the motorbike equipment and gear by Acerbis are off-road boots and body armor, bags and packs, disc covers and handguard, frame guards and motorcycle lights, plastic body parts, fuel tanks, etc<ref>{{cite web|title=Acerbis Inc: Products & Corporate Information |url=https://www.motorcycleid.com/images/acerbis/items/pdf/acerbis-product-catalog.pdf |date= 2018 |publisher=Acerbis Inc.}}</ref>.
==Sponsorship== The company is the sponsor of the Netherlands round of [[2017 Superbike World Championship]] (as Acerbis Dutch Round), as well as the shirt manufacturer of Italian football clubs: [[U.C. AlbinoLeffe|AlbinoLeffe]],<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.albinoleffe.com/albinoleffe-news/10435-albinoleffe-ubi-banca-ed-acerbis-insieme-per-non-fermarsi.html|title= AlbinoLeffe, UBI Banca ed Acerbis insieme per non… fermarsi! |date=1 August 2017|accessdate=25 July 2018|publisher=U.C. AlbinoLeffe|language=Italian}}</ref> [[Brescia Calcio|Brescia]]<ref>{{cite press release|url=http://www.bresciacalcio.it/stagione/news/3957-acerbis-e-il-brescia-calcio-insieme-fino-al-2019.html|title= ACERBIS e il Brescia Calcio insieme fino al 2019|date=3 July 2015|access-date=5 June 2017|publisher=Brescia Calcio|language=Italian}}</ref> and other teams.<ref name=officiallist/>
In [[2016 Superbike World Championship]] Acerbis sponsored the United Kingdom round.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.worldsbk.com/en/news/2017/Acerbis+launches+Official+WorldSBK+Riding+Gear+and+backs+Dutch+Round|title=Acerbis launches Official WorldSBK Riding Gear and backs Dutch Round|date=24 April 2017|access-date=5 June 2017|publisher=Superbike World Championship}}</ref>
