{{Infobox football biography | name = Brian Perez | image = | caption = | fullname = Brian Perez | birth_date = {{Birth date and age|1986|09|16|df=y}} | birth_place = [[Gibraltar]] | height = {{height|m=1.75}} | currentclub = [[Manchester 62 F.C.|Manchester 62]] | clubnumber = | position = [[Midfielder]] | youthyears1 = | youthclubs1 = | years1 = 2006–2015 | clubs1 = [[Lincoln Red Imps F.C.|Lincoln Red Imps]] | caps1 = | goals1 = | years2 = 2015–2017 | clubs2 = [[Manchester 62 F.C.|Manchester 62]] | caps2 = | goals2 = | years3 = 2017– | clubs3 = [[Manchester 62 F.C.|Manchester 62]] | caps3 = | goals3 = | nationalyears1 = 2014– | nationalteam1 = [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] | nationalcaps1= 1 | nationalgoals1 = 0 | pcupdate = 19:00, 9 September 2014 (UTC) | ntupdate = 9 September 2014 }}
'''Brian Perez''' (born 16 September 1986) is a Gibraltarian [[Association football|footballer]] who plays for [[Gibraltar Premier Division]] side [[Manchester 62 F.C.|Manchester 62]] and the [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] national team, where he plays as a [[Midfielder]].
==International career==
On 7 September 2014, Perez made his international début for [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]] in a [[UEFA Euro 2016 qualifying Group D|UEFA Euro 2016 Group D qualifying match]] against [[Poland national football team|Poland]] with Gibraltar losing 7-0.<ref>{{cite news|title=Gibraltar 0 - Poland 7|url=http://www1.skysports.com/football/live/match/308906|accessdate=9 September 2014|publisher=Sky Sports News|date=7 September 2014}}</ref>
===International statistics=== {{updated|7 September 2014}}.
