{{infobox country at games | NPC = MLT | NPCname = Malta Federation of Sports Associations for Disabled Persons | games = Summer Paralympics | year = 1960 | flagcaption = | oldcode = | website = | location = [[Rome]] | competitors = 4 | sports = 3 | flagbearer = | rank = | gold = 0 | silver = 2 | bronze = 2 | officials = | appearances = auto | app_begin_year = | app_end_year = | summerappearances = | winterappearances = | seealso = }} '''[[Malta]]''' participated in the '''[[1960 Summer Paralympics|inaugural Paralympic Games]]''' in 1960 in [[Rome]]. The country sent four representatives (three men and a woman) to compete in athletics, snooker and table tennis. Each of them won a medal in his or her event. Malta won more medals than at any other edition of the Paralympic Games, and won its only silver medals to date; it would win bronze, at best, in subsequent Games.<ref>[http://www.paralympic.org/Sport/Results/search.html?npc=MLT&gender=all&medal=all&sport=all&games=all Malta at the Paralympics], [[International Paralympic Committee]]</ref>
