===3rd ODI=== {{Limited overs matches | date = 5 September 2006 | time = 14:30 | daynight = yes | team1 = {{cr-rt|ENG}} | score1 = 271/9 (50 overs) | score2 = 274/8 (48.5 overs) | team2 = {{cr|PAK}} | runs1 = [[Jamie Dalrymple]] 62 (78) | wickets1 = [[Naved-ul-Hasan]] 4/57 (10 overs) | runs2 = [[Younis Khan]] 101 (109) | wickets2 = [[Stuart Broad]] 3/57 (10 over) | result = Pakistan won by 2 wickets | report = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/engvpak/engine/match/225247.html Scorecard] | venue = [[Rose Bowl (cricket ground)|Rose Bowl]], [[Southampton]] | umpires = [[Billy Doctrove]] (WI) and [[Nigel Llong]] | motm = [[Younis Khan]] (Pak) | toss = Pakistan won the toss and elected to field. }} Shoaib Akhtar was in the spotlight after television cameras caught him working on the ball. The pictures appeared to show Akhtar flicking his thumb at the ball. However, [[International Cricket Council|ICC]] referee [[Mike Procter]] analysed the TV footage and decided there was no case to answer on behalf of the Pakistani team.<ref>[http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/cricket/england/5312576.stm Match report] accessed 6 September 2006</ref>
