==Scotland ODI series== ===Only ODI=== {{Limited overs matches | date = 27 June 2006 | time = 10:45 | team1 = {{cr-rt|SCO}} | score1 = 203/8 (50 overs) | score2 = 205/5 (43.5 overs) | team2 = {{cr|PAK}} | runs1 = [[Ryan Watson (cricketer)|Ryan Watson]] 80 (85) | wickets1 = [[Shoaib Malik]] 3/35 (10 overs) | runs2 = [[Mohammad Yousuf (cricketer, born 1974)|Mohammad Yousuf]] 83[[Not out|*]] (113) | wickets2 = [[Paul Hoffmann (cricketer)|Paul Hoffmann]] 3/22 (10 overs) | result = Pakistan won by 5 wickets | report = [http://www.espncricinfo.com/engvpak/engine/match/240777.html Scorecard] | venue = [[Grange Cricket Club Ground]], [[Edinburgh]] | umpires = [[Daryl Hair]] (Aus) and [[Subhash Modi]] (Ken) | motm = [[Mohammad Yousuf (cricketer, born 1974)|Mohammad Yousuf]] (Pak) | toss = Pakistan won the toss and elected to field. | notes = [[Paul Hoffmann (cricketer)|Paul Hoffmann]], [[Dougie Lockhart]], [[Ross Lyons]], [[Neil McCallum (cricketer)|Neil McCallum]], [[Neil MacRae]], [[Dewald Nel]], [[Colin Smith (Scottish cricketer)|Colin Smith]] and [[Ryan Watson (cricketer)|Ryan Watson]] (all Sco) made their ODI debuts. }} Pakistan won the match by five wickets, after Scotland lost four wickets in the first eight overs and then four more in the remaining 42. [[Ryan Watson (cricketer)|Ryan Watson]] and [[Neil McCallum (cricketer)|Neil McCallum]] put on 116 for the fifth wicket, an ODI record partnership for [[Scotland national cricket team|Scotland]], who played their first ODI for seven years.<ref>[http://www.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/SCOT/BATTING/ODI_PARTNERSHIP_RECORDS_SCOT.html ODI Partnership Records for Scotland], from Cricinfo, retrieved 31 July 2006</ref> Their innings also doubled the number of ODI fifties scored for Scotland.<ref>[http://www.cricinfo.com/db/STATS/SCOT/BATTING/ODI_BAT_HIGH_INNS_SCORES_SCOT.html ODI Career Highest Individual Scores], from Cricinfo, retrieved 31 July 2006</ref>
