'''Sabin Marius Bornei''' (born January 5, 1975)<ref>{{cite news| url=https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/bo/sabin-marius-bornei-1.html | work=sports-reference.com | title=Sabin Marius Bornei | date=May 29, 2011}}</ref> is a retired [[amateur boxer]] from [[Romania]], who won a bronze medal in the [[light flyweight]] division (&ndash; 48&nbsp;kg) at the [[1996 European Amateur Boxing Championships]] in [[Vejle]], [[Denmark]]. Born in [[Bucharest]], he represented his native country in the juniorflyweight class at the [[1996 Summer Olympics]] in [[Atlanta, Georgia]], where he was eliminated in the second round by [[Thailand]]'s [[Somrot Kamsing]].

