{{Infobox cricket ground | ground_name = Spicers Sports Ground | nickname = | country = England | image = | location = [[Sawston]], [[Cambridgeshire]] | establishment = 1950 (first recorded match) | seating_capacity = | end1 = | end2 = | year1 = 1951-1967 | club1 = [[Cambridgeshire County Cricket Club|Cambridgeshire]] | date = 21 August | year = 2010 | source = https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/723.html Ground profile }}
'''Spicers Sports Ground''' is a [[cricket]] ground in [[Sawston]], [[Cambridgeshire]]. The first recorded match on the ground was in 1950, when [[Cambridgeshire County Cricket Club|Cambridgeshire]] played [[Huntingdonshire County Cricket Club|Huntingdonshire]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/723_misc.html Other matches played on Spicer's Sports Ground]</ref> The first [[Minor Counties Championship]] match held on the ground was in 1951, when Cambridgeshire played [[Hertfordshire County Cricket Club|Hertfordshire]]. From 1951 to 1967, the ground hosted 16 Minor Counties Championship matches, with the final Minor Counties fixture seeing Cambridgeshire entertain Hertfordshire.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/723_minc.html Minor Counties Championship Matches played on Spicers Sports Ground]</ref>
The ground has also held a single [[List-A cricket|List-A]] match when Cambridgeshire played [[Essex County Cricket Club|Essex]] in the [[1964 Gillette Cup]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/11/723_a.html List-A Matches played on Spicers Sports Ground]</ref> This match was Cambridgeshire's first List-A match.
In local domestic cricket, the ground is the home venue of Sawston Cricket Club<ref>[http://sawston.play-cricket.com/home/home.asp Sawston Cricket Club]</ref> who play in the Tucker Gardner Cambridgeshire and Huntingdonshire Cricket League First Division.
