'''Veer Surendra Sai Stadium''' is a cricket stadium in [[Sambalpur]], [[Orissa, India|Orissa]]. The ground is named after [[Surendra Sai]], an Indian freedom fighter who died fighting the British. The ground hosted cricket matches from 1973.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1205_f.html First-class matches]</ref> Till date ground has hosted 15 first-class matches. The ground has hosted at least one match since 2008 for [[Orissa cricket team]]. The ground hosted two [[List A]] matches in 1992 and 1999 both for [[East Zone cricket team|East Zone]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Grounds/14/1205_a.html List A]</ref>

