[[File:SWALEC Stand.jpg|thumb|right|SWALEC Stadium, Cardiff, home of the Welsh Cricket Association]]
The '''Welsh Cricket Association''' (WCA) (founded 1969) is the [[Governing bodies of sports in Wales|governing body]] of [[Wales|Welsh]] amateur [[cricket]]. It also runs the Welsh Cup and convenes the Welsh Coaching Forum. The WCA aims to promote, encourage, and improve amateur cricket in Wales, and to encourage and develop active participation in the game. Over 270 counties, associations, leagues and clubs are affiliated to the WCA.<ref name="CCC 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.sports-council-wales.org.uk/grants-funding/funding/list-of-bodies |title=Governing Bodies of Sport-Sports Council for Wales |publisher=[[Sport Wales]] |year=2007 |accessdate=2009-07-23 |work=Sport Wales Chwaraeon Cymru website |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20081015213305/http://www.sports-council-wales.org.uk/grants-funding/funding/list-of-bodies |archivedate=October 15, 2008 }}</ref><ref name="BCC 1">{{cite web|url=http://www.cbw.org.uk/|title=WLBU|publisher=The Cricket Board of Wales|year=2009|accessdate=2009-07-11|work=Cricket Board of Wales website}}</ref><ref name="WCA 3">{{cite web|url=http://www.welshcricket.org/|title=Welsh Cricket Association|publisher=Welsh Cricket Association|year=2009|accessdate=2009-07-13|work=Welsh Cricket Association website}}</ref><ref name="WCA 4">{{cite web|url=http://www.welshcricket.org/constitution.htm/ |title=Welsh Cricket Association - Constitution |publisher=Welsh Cricket Association |year=2009 |accessdate=2009-07-13 |work=Welsh Cricket Association website |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20071006160956/http://www.welshcricket.org/constitution.htm |archivedate=October 6, 2007 }}</ref><ref name="WCA 5">{{cite web|url=http://www.welshcricket.org/affiliate.htm|title=Welsh Cricket Association - Affiliated Bodies|publisher=Welsh Cricket Association|year=2009|accessdate=2009-07-13|work=Welsh Cricket Association website}}</ref>

The Welsh Cricket Association is based at the [[SWALEC Stadium]], [[Sophia Gardens]], [[Cardiff]].<ref name="BCC 1"/>

